Joe Jeffries v. The State. No. 22300. Delivered November 18, 1942.

The opinion states the case.

No attorney for appellant. Spurgeon E. Bell, State’s Attorney, of Austin, for the State. BEAUCHAMP, Judge.

*54The appellant was assessed a fine of $150.00 upon his plea of guilty to a complaint charging a violation of the liquor laws.

The appeal presents nothing for our consideration and the judgment of the trial court is affirmed.
